g.text: Note: manually added some extra thicc traces
on some of the GND_motor pads, where
appropriate for handling a lot of current
Note: J30 uses thick traces for power
lines so that it *could* be used for higher current
external applications
Note: T7 - T12 (large pad test points) and LED
signals use thin traces because they don’t need
much current. J20 uses thick traces for power
lines so that it *could* be used for higher current
external applications
Note: it’s fine that the 5V plane is a little thin up
here in the motor connector pandhandle part
of the board. Only the corner servos draw their
motor current from 5V, whereas the drive motors
draw motor current from the roboclaw RC*M*A/B
lines. The thinest bit, about 2.5mm, should be more
than enough copper to handle the current.
